are of agro control. I see no reason that you have to use willsapper for agro control in any situation.<br><br>If the mobs not on you and your saying &quot;please proc, please proc, please proc&quot; then something has gone wrong already. Already your doing thens badly.<br><br>Solo agro time should be all you need, I havnt seen it fail yet. And for tank switches we send the tanks in at different times. MT 6sec later the first switch tank and so on then all other melee.<br><br>I have a willsapper, and a skybreaker so I have used both. I taunt off people with sod's when i need to. I am not just talking out of my butt. <br><br>All I am saying, is counting on a proc for agro is wrong. Procs should be an extra, a buffer that makes you feel good. Not something you &quot;must&quot; have to win. <p><br>Gore Bloodlust<br>60th Iksar Warlord ( Dead Sexy )<br>Proud member of Fire & Fury<br><a href="http://www.huffnet.net/fire&fury">Fire & Fury Website</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67224">My Stuff</a><br><a href="http://www.clicksmilie.de" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.huffnet.net/fire&fury/Roster/Gore4.JPG" border="0"></a> <br>Life, Liberty, and the pursuit of all who threaten it.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uqxired.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Q Xired</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/24/02 8:20:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1700.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I went a long, long, long time using 2 weapons that had no proc on them. I never had trouble getting/holding aggro most of the time. Proc's certainly help out getting a